parameters: Several days later, on a certain day.

Rise's voice, in response to Suelle's joyful one, sounded
somewhat disheartened.

Rise hesitated for a moment with her gestures, but
eventually began to speak slowly.

"These past few days, I've been looking into Selphie and
Tina's whereabouts on my own, but I haven't found anything."

"I see. But I've finished preparing too, so let's search
together. We'll definitely find them."
Rise slowly shook her head at Suelle's words.

"It's not that. It would be more accurate to say there were
too few clues to find."
"Well, let me put it another way."

"It's not just that there was not a single clue; I can't
even remember what I investigated."

"Feeling doubtful about that, I started keeping a record of
my actions."

"And then, there were clearly several instances where there
were gaps in the record."

"I can't remember anything about those time periods. But the
strange thing is, I can't seem to feel any discomfort about
it."

"The fact that I can't feel any discomfort is itself
discomforting."

"Yes, it's likely that I... was brainwashed without
realizing it at some point."

"They were so kind as to only bring back my consciousness,
while rewriting my memory as they pleased."
A shadow falls over Rise's face.

She might be considering whether she herself has been
leaking information about Tina and Selphie.

Rise, unable to hide her unstable feelings, confides in her
companion Suelle.

"I see. But if that's the case, what I've prepared might
come in handy."

However, the words that came back were not what Rise had
expected.

"What you've prepared? Now that you mention it, you did say
something you were making was completed."

"Yes. Although I'm half-doubtful whether it will work or
not."
Saying so, Suelle takes out a device shaped like a glove.

"I was thinking about the brainwashing of Tina and Selphie,
and whether it's brainwashing or something else, a long-
distance skill that imparts some effect on another person's
body, you know."

"The question was, where does the power come from in the
first place?"
Suelle continues to explain as he formulates a hypothesis.

"The same goes for this slave spell. If there's a mechanism
that releases it upon breach of contract,"

"Then I thought there must be some connection and shared
power between them during that time."

Suelle explains that otherwise, it would be strange for both
contracts to be released simultaneously at the time of
contract termination.
"I see. So that's where this device comes in?"

"Yes, originally it was made to deflect skill attacks, but
this is an adapted and improved version."

"It's designed to create a thin membrane that envelops the
entire body and blocks the flow of power itself."

That is, of course, if there really is a flow of power, he
adds.

"If that's the case, it could be just what we need. Try it
on me."

"Yeah, I understand. Actually, I was also worried about what
would happen if we found Selphie and the others and it
turned out the device didn't work."
Suelle slips on the gloves he had prepared with a snap.

"Okay, let's start. But Rise, I need you to take off all
your clothes except for the gloves."

"No, I don't want to be lusted after at a time like this.
Can't it wait until after we've saved Tina and Selphie?"

"I know. It's because I'm cute, right? You couldn't control
your desires, could you?"

Rise: "But why leave the gloves on? Are you some kind of
pervert?"

"No, that's not it!! It's necessary for the activation of
this device!!"

Suelle: "The hands are where the magic flows through when
casting spells, so there shouldn't be a long-term pipeline
connected there, which means it's not a problem!!"
"I'm just joking. I understand that much."
"I've taken everything off. So, what should I do next?"

"Hey, you're making me feel embarrassed with that
attitude..."

"Sorry!! So, first I need to channel power into this device
and touch your entire body."
"This method of use sounds kind of erotic..."

"Well, it doesn't have the operability to change shape to
fit the body yet..."
Suelle clears his throat and continues to explain.

"This glove-type device creates a membrane that blocks the
power of the spells at the touched locations."

"If I touch your entire body and wrap it with a membrane
that blocks from the outside, the power lines should be
interrupted."

Once it comes off after a certain amount of time, the flow
of power, like a circuit, should be unable to reconnect and
be completely blocked, Suelle added.

"I see. Certainly, if there's something like power lines and
they get disconnected, we could crush anything, ancient
spell formulas or whatever, without regard to the structure
of power."

"Yeah, even if it's an ancient spell formula, I think it
still needs power lines."

Even if it's an ancient spell formula, the laws of power and
the essence of power are just different.

If there was a flow of power in the spell formula, then it
could be removed, even if it's a type of power that isn't
recognized as a skill.

Suelle approached Rise's body with his fingers slowly, a
tense expression on his face.
"Hey, can I ask you one question?"

Startled by Rise's voice while he was tense, Suelle let out
a strange sound.

Even Rise seemed a bit taken aback by Suelle's excessive
attitude.

"Yeah, if you try to create a membrane with your own power
on yourself, it will mix with the power inside your body and
the blocking membrane won't form properly."

"Hmm, well, I was just curious. It doesn't really matter
either way."
"Sorry for stopping you. Let's really start this time."
Suelle: "Then this time for sure, let's begin?"

"The biggest change is that your face is bright red and
you're bleeding from your nose."
"That's, that's not important!! What about you, Rise?"

Suddenly, Rise was struck by nausea and a headache. At the
same time, memories of the past began to flood into her
mind.
